# 🧹 Kubernetes Deletion Cheat Sheet

---

## 🔹 1. Delete PODS

### Delete a single Pod

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
```

### Delete all Pods in a namespace

```bash
kubectl delete pods --all -n <namespace>
```

### Force delete a stuck Pod

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name> -n <namespace> --grace-period=0 --force
```

---

## 🔹 2. Delete DEPLOYMENTS

### Delete a Deployment

```bash
kubectl delete deployment <deployment-name> -n <namespace>
```

### Delete all Deployments in a namespace

```bash
kubectl delete deployments --all -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 3. Delete STATEFULSETS

```bash
kubectl delete statefulset <statefulset-name> -n <namespace>
```

⚠️ **PVCs are NOT deleted automatically**

---

## 🔹 4. Delete SERVICES

### Delete Service

```bash
kubectl delete service <service-name> -n <namespace>
```

### Delete all Services

```bash
kubectl delete services --all -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 5. Delete CONFIGMAPS

```bash
kubectl delete configmap <configmap-name> -n <namespace>
```

Delete all:

```bash
kubectl delete configmaps --all -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 6. Delete SECRETS

```bash
kubectl delete secret <secret-name> -n <namespace>
```

Delete all (⚠️ careful):

```bash
kubectl delete secrets --all -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 7. Delete PVC / PV

### Delete PVC

```bash
kubectl delete pvc <pvc-name> -n <namespace>
```

### Delete PV

```bash
kubectl delete pv <pv-name>
```

Check reclaim policy before deleting PV:

```bash
kubectl get pv
```

---

## 🔹 8. Delete JOBS & CRONJOBS

### Delete Job

```bash
kubectl delete job <job-name> -n <namespace>
```

### Delete CronJob

```bash
kubectl delete cronjob <cronjob-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 9. Delete DAEMONSETS

```bash
kubectl delete daemonset <daemonset-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 10. Delete HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler)

```bash
kubectl delete hpa <hpa-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 11. Delete INGRESS

```bash
kubectl delete ingress <ingress-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 12. Delete NAMESPACE (🔥 DANGEROUS)

```bash
kubectl delete namespace <namespace>
```

💥 Deletes EVERYTHING inside:

* Pods
* Services
* PVCs
* ConfigMaps
* Secrets

---

## 🔹 13. Delete by LABEL (VERY POWERFUL)

Delete all resources with label:

```bash
kubectl delete all -l app=job-service -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 14. Delete EVERYTHING in a Namespace (⚠️)

```bash
kubectl delete all --all -n <namespace>
```

Does NOT delete:

* PVCs
* ConfigMaps
* Secrets

To wipe namespace fully:

```bash
kubectl delete namespace <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 15. Troubleshooting Deletions

### Pod stuck in `Terminating`

```bash
kubectl get pod <pod-name> -n <ns> -o yaml
```

Remove finalizers:

```bash
kubectl patch pod <pod-name> -n <ns> -p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":null}}'
```

---

## 🔹 16. Cleanup CrashLoop / Image Errors

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
```

Kubernetes will recreate it (Deployment/StatefulSet)

---

## 🧠 Golden Rules

| Action             | Result                 |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Delete Pod         | Recreated (if managed) |
| Delete Deployment  | Pods gone              |
| Delete StatefulSet | Pods gone, PVC stays   |
| Delete Namespace   | Everything gone        |

---

## 📌 Daily Use Shortlist (MEMORIZE)

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod> -n <ns>
kubectl delete deploy <name> -n <ns>
kubectl delete svc <name> -n <ns>
kubectl delete pvc <name> -n <ns>
kubectl delete ns <ns>
```

